snippet.textDisplay: Constructed by Landgrave William IV from 1584 to 1618 in Schmalken Thuringer the Schloss Wilhelmsburg is a palace made out of white stones on the outer construction and wood in the inside. It was used as a noble palace with a church and a ball room however today it is a museum that is open from Tuesday to Sunday, from 10 am to 4pm, the price to get in as an adult is 6 euros, as a child 4 euros, in a group of 10 it would cost 5 euros a person and finally as a family it is 12 euros. The castle is know for it's garden, it's beutiful decoration and it hosts one of the oldest protestant church.
